newsitem.title: USA: FCOJ weekly movement up to 5.100 million gallons.
newsitem.headline: FCOJ weekly movement up to 5.100 million gallons.

text.p: Florida Citrus Processors Association said frozen concentrated orange juice movement into trade channels for the week ended Sept 28 was 5,100,274 gallons, up from 4,803,156 gallons last week.
Imports were 202,914 gallons compared with 93,493 gallons the previous week, and domestic receipts totaled 35,851 gallons versus none a week ago.
Retail movement was 1,167,789 gallons compared with 939,275 gallons last year, while bulk movement was 3,397,759 gallons versus 4,088,050 gallons last year.
Current season cumulative movement was 226,195,831 versus 226,017,473 a year ago.
The final total pack for the season is 202,353,371 against 216,502,392 a year ago.
